text:
Hey hey :wave: wondering how everyone is handling <https://knowledge.HubSpot.com/resources/what-are-the-submission-requirements-for-the-template-marketplace#1-4|this Marketplace guideline> regarding 3rd party asset loading in Themes: "...If an external CDN version of a library is included, a local copy must be provided as a fallback." I'm thinking of doing something like this (below) but is this best practice? Is there a slicker, perhaps more HubL-y way to handle this?:

```{# AOS #}
{{ require_js("<https://unpkg.com/aos@next/dist/aos.js>") }}
...
...
{{ standard_footer_includes }}
{% require_js %}
  &lt;script&gt;
    if(!AOS) { 
      ..load local copy
    }
  &lt;/script&gt;
{% end_require_js %} ```
